   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-one THE SURPASSING SALVATION Scripture: Eph 2:4-8 The source of salvation The source of salvation is God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The source of salvation is God s mercy.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The source of salvation is God s great love.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The accomplishment of salvation Salvation is accomplished through the death and resurrection of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Salvation is also accomplished through the ascension of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The surpassing salvation When we were dead in sin, God s surpassing salvation caused us to become alive together with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>He also caused us to be raised together with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>There is a difference between being made alive and being raised.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To be made alive means to have life; to be raised means not only to have life but to be able to move.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Not only was Lazarus enlivened in the tomb, but his coming out of the tomb shows that he was resurrected, that he was raised up.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Thirdly, He caused us to sit together with Him in heavenly places.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>This is surpassing!</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This is God s surpassing salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The manifestation of salvation This salvation manifests the rich and abundant grace of God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>This grace is given to us in God s kindness.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Emphasize that grace is God s action in freely saving us.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Emphasize that kindness issues out of God s mercy and love, out of the intent of His heart.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>How to receive this salvation</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Stress the matter of faith.</S>
   </TEXT>
